    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix IMEISV digit extraction in UICC interface\n\n### Summary\nThe `getImeisvDigit()` function in the UICC interface was not properly handling edge cases which could lead to incorrect IMEISV reporting in NAS messages. This fix improves error handling and parameter validation.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/UICC/usim_interface.c`: Enhanced `getImeisvDigit()` with proper NULL checks, bounds checking, and digit validation\n- `openair3/UICC/usim_interface.h`: No changes needed to function signature\n\n### Reproduction\nWithout this fix, when the UE configuration contains an IMEISV string shorter than 16 digits or containing non-digit characters, the function may return incorrect values or potentially cause undefined behavior. This can be observed in the Registration Request messages where the IMEISV identity IE contains garbage values instead of the expected device identifier.\n\nTo reproduce:\n1. Configure UE with IMEISV string shorter than 16 digits\n2. Initiate a registration procedure\n3. Observe incorrect IMEISV values in the Registration Request message\n\nThe fix ensures that invalid IMEISV configurations are handled gracefully with appropriate logging while maintaining compatibility with existing valid configurations.\n"
}